<!-- Node: "Id Software and Guildhall" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Id Software and Guildhall</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/1804" title="View user profile.">Kingpin_Xatrix</a> on Saturday, April 24, 2004 - 14:22</small><br /><br />
<a href = "http://www.guildhall.smu.edu/">Guildhall</a>, a school for video game designers and programmers that is taught by professionals from the industry in various fields has only been around for about a year now but is becoming one of the premiere spots for game creation talent. Recently <a href = "http://www.idsoftware.com/">Id Software</a> hired Brian Harris, an intern from Guildhall. Read what <b>Tim Willits</b> has to say about that <a href = "http://www.guildhall.smu.edu/news/id-Intern.htm">school</a>.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/comment/reply/246" title="Add a new comment to this page.">Add new comment</a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "Softimage for Half-Life2 Video Tutorial" -->
<div class="body_box_header">Softimage for Half-Life2 Video Tutorial</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/1804" title="View user profile.">Kingpin_Xatrix</a> on Saturday, April 24, 2004 - 14:12</small><br /><br />
<b>Softimage</b> has put out a set of 4 videos as a video tutorial of Softimage XSI for <b>Half Life 2</b> (made during the recent GDC). Softimage XSI is the 3D graphics package that Valve is promoting as their preferential platform for mod makers for the Half-Life 2 engine. Visit <a href = "http://www.filerush.com/download.php?target=softimage_for_hl2_tut.zip">filerush</a> for files.
<br /><br />
<a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/comment/reply/245" title="Add a new comment to this page.">Add new comment</a>
</div><br />


<!-- Node: "UT2004 UnrealScript Development Environment Released" -->
<div class="body_box_header">UT2004 UnrealScript Development Environment Released</div>
<div class="body_box"><small>Submitted by <a href="http://www.gamedesign.net/user/view/204" title="View user profile.">Miniwood</a> on Wednesday, April 21, 2004 - 22:10</small><br /><br />
Steven Polge, coder at Epic, has announced:

<BLOCKQUOTE>The UT2004 UnrealScript Development Environment is now available for UT2004 mod programmers, at:<BR><BR> <A HREF="http://unreal.epicgames.com/Files/UDE3005.zip">http://unreal.epicgames.com/Files/UDE3005.zip</a>. <BR><BR>UnrealScript coders should also download the UT2004 v3186 UnrealScript source code, from:<BR><BR> <A HREF="http://unreal.epicgames.com/Files/scripts3186.zip">http://unreal.epicgames.com/Files/scripts3186.zip</A>. <BR><BR>Both programmers and level designers will find the Level and Mod Optimization guide useful:<BR><BR> 
<A HREF="http://unreal.epicgames.com/Files/optimization-guide.txt">http://unreal.epicgames.com/Files/optimization-guide.txt</A></BLOCKQUOTE>
<BR><BR>
<br /><br />
